				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The French NES uses a custom AV/RF/AC module which converts the composite video from the NES board to RGB output. It has nothing to do with the PPU.
<br />
<br />If you want, you could buy a French NES (if you can find one) and desolder the modules then swap them around.
<br />
<br />
<br />French NES also uses a custom video cable only available in the same places it was. Unless you want to do some creative rewiring, its advisable to get one of those as well.
<br />If you're in PAL territory I'm guessing you'd have SCART. IIRC thats what the FR NES video cable outputs to.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.vgchat.com/signaturepics/sigpic30_2.gif" alt="Image" />
